# CI/CD Flow for Cloud Module

The Pipeline will be triggered upon the following events:

1. Code Push to Gitlab by Developer / Successful Branch Merge
2. Creation of Merge Request by Developer

**According to standard practices, will run pipeline only for specific branches &amp; refs.**

1. 8.x-\* : This regex  match the branches where different versions of module are maintained.
2. Merge Requests: This will reference to all the open merge requests to the Above Mentioned Branches.

     Pipeline Stages for the Code Push and Merge Requests will be Common, while for Merge Requests Different Stages will be run.

Following are the events that will take place in the pipeline:

1. Code Push to Gitlab by Developer / Successful Branch Merge

Upon Code Push / Successful Merge, the CI Pipeline will run following   stages.

**Test:** This stage will run all the necessary tests concurrently.

**On Success** : it will notify the concerned persons, and Proceed to the next Stage.

**On Failure:** it will notify the concerned persons with the job url, and stop the pipeline.

**Build:** After the Tests are successful, the build stage will build the docker

images with the new code and push to the gitlab docker registry.

**On Success** : it will notify the concerned persons, and Proceed to the next Stage.

**On Failure:** it will notify the concerned persons with the job url, and stop the pipeline.

**Deploy:** After the image build is successful, the project will be deployed

 To Gitlab Integrated Kubernetes Cluster.

   **On Success:** It will notify the concerned person with the environment URL and environment management URL.

   **On Failure:** it will notify the concerned persons with the job url, and stop the pipeline.



1. Code Push to Gitlab by Developer / Successful Branch Merge

Upon Creation of  Merge Request, the CI Pipeline will run following   stages.

**Test:** This stage will run all the necessary tests concurrently.

**On Success** : it will notify the concerned persons, and Proceed to the next Stage.

E.g [https://gitlab.dataninja.net/root/cloud/-/jobs/409](https://gitlab.dataninja.net/root/cloud/-/jobs/409)

**On Failure:** it will notify the concerned persons with the job url, and stop the pipeline.

**Build:** After the Tests are successful, the build stage will build the docker

images with the new code and push to the gitlab docker registry.

**On Success** : it will notify the concerned persons, and Proceed to the next Stage.

E.g https://gitlab.dataninja.net/root/cloud/-/jobs/410

**On Failure:** it will notify the concerned persons with the job url, and stop the pipeline.

**Deploy:** After the image build is successful, the preview will be deployed

 To Gitlab Integrated Kubernetes Cluster.

   **On Success:** It will notify the concerned person with the preview environment URL and environment management URL.

  E.g [https://gitlab.dataninja.net/root/cloud/environments](https://gitlab.dataninja.net/root/cloud/environments)

  E.g [http://cloud.testing.dataninja.net](http://cloud.testing.dataninja.net)

   **On Failure:** it will notify the concerned persons with the job url, and stop the pipeline.
